# JavaScript Conventions

## Module Pattern

Every component module exports a single `init` function:

```js
export function initComponentName() {
    // DOM queries, event bindings, logic
}
```

Called from `app/pages/index.js` inside `DOMContentLoaded`.

## Style Rules

- `'use strict'` only in the entry point (`index.js`)
- 4-space indentation, single quotes, trailing commas (ES5)
- Arrow functions for callbacks with single param omit parens: `x => x + 1`
- Constants in UPPER_SNAKE_CASE at the top of the function scope
- Use `document.getElementById` / `document.querySelectorAll` for DOM access

## Imports

- Styles: `import '#/styles/globals.css'`
- Utils: `import { helper } from '#/utils/helper'`
- Components: `import { initX } from '@/atoms/x'` or `@/molecules/x`

## Event Listeners

```js
// Always specify passive when no preventDefault is needed
element.addEventListener('scroll', handler, { passive: true });
```

## Accessibility

- Check `isPrefersReducedMotion()` before smooth scrolling or animations
- Check `isMobile()` before desktop-only features (custom cursor)
- Guard missing DOM elements with early return + `console.error`
